.TH recon 1  "recon " 
.SH NAME
recon \- Origin discovery via crt.sh + DNS (authorized targets only)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrecon\fR <\fB\-\-domain\fR> [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Origin discovery via crt.sh + DNS (authorized targets only)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-domain\fR \fI<DOMAIN>\fR
Target domain to discover origin IPs for (e.g., example.com)
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: text]
Output format. `text` (default) is human\-friendly with hints; `json` is a stable, machine\-parseable surface for piping into jq, ansible, or downstream automation. JSON output suppresses the human stdout decoration
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
text
.IP \(bu 2
json
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
